        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://galactic-forensics.github.io/blog/posts/06-box-why/"/>
        <id>https://galactic-forensics.github.io/blog/posts/06-box-why/</id>
        
        <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;The python ecosystem has changed a lot over the last year,
especially with respect to tooling.
The usage of &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;rust-lang.org&quot;&gt;Rust&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; has opened new, very fast,
and by now very popular tools
that aid in linting (&lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;astral.sh&#x2F;ruff&quot;&gt;ruff&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;) and
package management (&lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;astral.sh&#x2F;uv&quot;&gt;uv&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;rye.astral.sh&quot;&gt;rye&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;).
But what tools are there if you want to share your python applications
with colleagues that do not use python?&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</summary>
        
